```sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription + event_month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry
WITH base AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.status,
        b.event_month,
        b.amount
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_billing') }} b
        ON b.subscription_id = s.subscription_id
)
SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('month', base.event_month) AS month,
    COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
    COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT base.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(base.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT base.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM base
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
    ON p.plan_id = base.plan_id
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
    ON u.user_id = base.user_id
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
    ON c.company_id = u.company_id
GROUP BY
    DATE_TRUNC('month', base.event_month),
    COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)'),
    COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)')
ORDER BY month ASC, tier ASC, industry ASC
